  - STATE_UPDATE: {'commit_analysis_result': '**Analysis Summary:**\n\nI analyzed the build error for the `bls-signatures` project with error time `2025-2-23`. The error occurs during compilation of the `arkworks-algebra` module in cryptofuzz, specifically in the JSON library header file with deprecated literal operator syntax.\n\n**Key Findings:**\n\n1. **Error Source**: The compilation fails in `/src/cryptofuzz/modules/arkworks-algebra/module.cpp` due to deprecated literal operator declarations in the JSON library (`json.hpp` lines 22514 and 22533).\n\n2. **Root Cause**: The build uses `-Werror` flag which treats warnings as errors, and the JSON library contains deprecated syntax (`operator"" _json` and `operator"" _json_pointer`) that triggers `-Wdeprecated-literal-operator` warnings.\n\n3. **Build Configuration**: The current `build.sh` file already has `-Wno-deprecated-literal-operator` flags added to suppress this warning for most modules including arkworks-algebra, but the error still occurs suggesting the flag might not be propagating correctly to the actual compiler command.\n\n4. **Git History Analysis**: \n   - No commits found around the error date `2025-2-23`\n   - The original `build.sh` (commit `d03a9ed`) didn\'t have any `-Wno-deprecated-literal-operator` flags\n   - All other commits are from fix attempts by our system\n   - The error appears to be environmental (compiler version/library version mismatch) rather than a code change\n\n**Conclusion**: No specific Git commit was found that introduced the build error. The issue appears to be related to compiler/library version compatibility rather than a code change. The file `generated_prompt_file/commit_changed.txt` has been created with "No relevant commit found."'}
